main event: A round object bigger than a basketball, with spines sticking out, was observed in the sky over Great Neck, New York on December 2, 1957.
interesting points: The object was observed for 5 minutes, moving from north to south.
The object had no visible vapor trail.
The object made a buzzing sound.
The sighting was made by a civilian observer, a 15-year-old from Great Neck, New York.
The weather conditions were clear, with good visibility.
sighted object: Round object bigger than a basketball, with spines sticking out
